Problems.Description: When during downswing, the body approaches the ball causing impact to occur prematurely.
When the clubhead moves inside the swing path during takeback.
When the right elbow excessively flares out like a chicken wing at the top of the backswing.
When swinging causes the club to excessively go behind the head at the top of the backswing.
When the upper body bends forward during address.
When balance is not maintained and collapses at finish.
